the family of a 13yearold girl who died after 
a failed abortion has received a 12 million jury award the 
largest wrongfuldeath abortion payment in state history 
a manhattan jury made its decision last friday in the case of 
dawn ravenell who died in january 1985 after the abortion at the 
eastern womens center in manhattan 
the jury ruled that dr allen klein of philadelphia and nurse 
robert augente of east williston ny were liable for 950000 in 
pecuniary damages or loss of service to the family and 275000 
for pain and suffering 
the girls parents who are both pentecostal ministers did not 
know their daughter was pregnant until they received word she was 
in a coma on jan 24 1985 said the girls mother ruth ravenell 
i know that she was fearful in that we are a religious 
family said mrs ravenell i think that she felt that for me 
to see her as less than perfect would have been too much 
according to court records ravenell was 21 weeks pregnant when 
she went to the clinic for an abortion 
five minutes into the procedure ravenell came out of a general 
anesthesia and began vomiting and choking court papers said the 
doctor and nurse inserted a breathing tube and moved her to a 
recovery room where she began choking again papers said 
she then suffered a massive heart attack before the medical 
personnel checked on her again according to the records she was 
already in a coma when the ambulance arrived she died three weeks 
later at roosevelt hospital never regaining consciousness 
nationally six women died from abortions in 1985 according to 
the alan guttmacher institute a reproductive health research 
organization 
before fridays award the highest sum awarded in an abortion 
death was 701500 in the 1984 case of a 24yearold manhattan 
woman said russell moran editor of jury verdict reporter 
