here is a list of some of the contraceptive 
options available in the united states and their firstyear failure 
rates the figures are from the alan guttmacher institute except 
the norplant figure is from the population council 
the figure given is the proportion of women relying on the 
specified method of contraception for a year who can be expected to 
get pregnant during that time 
norplant 02 percent 
oral contraceptives 01 percent to 6 percent for combination 
pills and 05 percent for progestinonly pills 
intrauterine device or iud 1 percent to 2 percent 
condom 1416 percent 
diaphragm 1416 percent 
natural family planning 1416 percent 
vasectomy 01 percent 
sterilization 02 percent 
