gremitskikh said 
his constructive activity was especially appreciable and 
fruitful in the periods of coolness in the relations between the 
ussr and the united states gremitskikh said he always 
raised his voice and in addressing leaders of both superpowers 
spoke out in favor of overcoming difficulties and for fruitful 
cooperation in all spheres 
hammers involvement in the soviet union began in 1921 as a 
young doctor just out of medical school who came to the country to 
help in famine relief 
he met with vladimir lenin and sought his help in 
reestablishing trade between the communist regime and the west he 
worked out a deal to trade surplus us grain for soviet products 
at one point hammer was sole representative for 38 us 
companies in the soviet union and also owned and operated an 
asbestos mine and founded the first pencil factory in the nation 
during one visit to the soviet union he said ill never 
forget what lenin told me during one of our meetings he said dr 
hammer we dont need doctors we need business people who can do 
things that was the end of my promising medical career 
hammer maintained his ties to the soviet union from the lenin 
years to the era of perestroika initiated by gorbachev he met with 
every soviet leader since lenin 
he always raised his voice and in addressing leaders of both 
superpowers spoke out in favor of overcoming difficulties and for 
fruitful cooperation in all spheres gremitskikh said 
one of his largest developments in moscow is the huge 
mezhdunarodnaya hotel and sovincenter exhibition complex built on 
the banks of the moscow river it is known in the city as the 
hammer center 
