female are sure to survive at this point 
most giant pandas born in captivity die in their first weks 
and scientists are not sure why 
zhang said the problem was especially acute with pandas 
conceived through artificial insemination as the twins were it 
also is rare for both twin pandas to survive because mother pandas 
frequently take care of one and neglect the other 
zhang said the female cubs weight had increased from 53 ounces 
when it was born aug 24 to more than 13 pounds as of monday the 
males weight increased from 5 ounces to 13 pounds 
they were born at the chengdu zoo in southwestern china which 
has an active program of inseminating captive pandas the procedure 
is controversial among scientists many foreign wildlife experts 
argue that it would be better to reproduce conditions in the wild 
to encourage mating and natural pregnancies 
xinhua said only 24 of the 1155 pandas born worldwide as a 
result of artificial insemination have survived the twins mother 
qingqing was herself the product of artificial insemination 
china has the worlds only wild panda population but its 
