<TEXT>
armand hammers nearly 70 years of contact with 
the soviet union left an indelible mark on this country from 
memorabilia enshrined in vladimir lenins apartment to a modern 
capitalist trade center in moscow 
hammer 92 who died monday in los angeles received official 
adulation in the soviet union while bringing him some scorn in his 
native united states for dealing with the nations former cold war 
enemy 
president mikhail s gorbachev sent a message of condolence to 
the hammers family and said he was associated with one of the 
most remarkable pages in ussoviet relations 
foreign ministry spokesman yuri gremitskikh said the charismatic 
entrepreneur will be remembered for his tireless efforts to 
maintain good relations with the kremlin 
it is a big loss said dr matt shatz a producer at armand 
hammer productions a moscow filmmaking company hammer founded 12 
years ago 
he put all his strength into this company shatz said 
hammer made many trips to the soviet union the first in 1921 as 
a 23yearold doctor just out of columbia university medical 
school hammer the son of a russianborn father arrived as the 
soviet union suffered famine exacerbated by world war i 
he met lenin the soviet founder and was enlisted to help 
reestablish trade between the communist government and the west 
hammers first deal was us grain for soviet products 
hammer stayed in the country until 1930 becoming an executive 
of the amalgamated american co which the state news agency tass 
said was founded with lenins personal approval tass said 
during a later visit to the soviet union he said ill never 
forget what lenin told me during one of our meetings he said dr 
hammer we dont need doctors we need business people who can do 
things that was the end of my promising medical career 
hammer chairman of occidental petroleum corp became a 
representative of 38 foreign companies in the soviet union he 
owned and operated an asbestos mine and founded the first pencil 
factory in the ussr 
visitors to lenins meticulously preserved apartment in the 
kremlin can see four of the pencils standing in a holder on lenins 
desk 
guides also point proudly to a black leather chair where hammer 
sat during his meetings with the revolutionary leader and to a 
small stature of monkey sitting contemplatively on charles darwins 
book origin of the species hammer had given the sculpture to 
lenin as a gift 
hammer met with dictator josef stalin but the two could not 
work together and hammer ended up selling his enterprises to the 
soviet government after stalins death hammer resumed his efforts 
that melded business and politics 
he will live in history as well as in peoples memories as 
an entrepreneur who made cooperation by his country with the soviet 
union possible in the years when nobody dared to even think about 
it read an unsigned obituary in the government newspaper 
izvestia 
in 1978 thensoviet leader leonid brezhnev awarded hammer the 
order of friendship between peoples in honor of his 80th birthday 
and help in establishing better ussoviet relations 
at the same time hammer was wrapping up a deal to split the 
cost of a huge new international trade center in moscow the 
center built for the 1980 moscow olympic games houses the huge 
mezhdunarodnaya hotel and sovincenter exhibition complex it is 
known as the hammer center and is one of the citys most modern 
office complexes 
after the chernobyl nuclear power plant explosion in 1986 
hammer personally helped bring a bone marrow specialist dr robert 
gale to the soviet union along with costly medicine and equipment 
for operations 
throughout the 1970s and 1980s hammer cultivated his passion 
for art and presided over the opening of several exhibits and 
galleries he handed over historical relics including letters by 
lenin to the soviets 
