global wheat stockpiles continue at record 
high levels putting a damper on us exports and market prices an 
agriculture department report showed tuesday 
overall 199091 wheat production forecasts increased from a 
month ago with gains in canada china and mexico more than 
offsetting reduced prospects in brazil the european community and 
south africa 
the projected average us market price was reduced 5 cents a 
bushel from november to a range of 250 to 270 for the 
marketing year that began june 1 in the previous two years the 
farm price of wheat was 372 per bushel 
according to the new supplyanddemand report exports are still 
expected to be 1075 billion bushels in 199091 down from 1233 
billion last year 
the us wheat stockpile carried over next june 1 into the new 
harvest and marketing year was projected at 937 million bushels 
down slightly from the november outlook but still much larger than 
the 536 million bushels carried forward last june 1 
looking at corn and other coarse grains the report showed 
global production in 199091 and the yearending stockpile to be up 
slightly from last month 
although prolonged dry conditions have cut corn planting in 
south africa gains in the ec canada and turkey are more than 
offsetting the report said the smaller crop likely will 
eliminate corn exports by south africa during their 199091 
marketing year 
as with wheat farmers harvested a bumper corn crop this year 
however unlike wheat total corn use is expected to exceed output 
meaning some reduction in the stockpile during the 199091 
marketing year that began on sept 1 
consequently corn prices at the farm are projected to average 
220 to 250 per bushel this season compared with 236 in 
198990 
the corn stockpile next sept 1 was projected at 1236 billion 
bushels down from 1344 billion estimated this sept 1 
world oilseed production including us soybeans also is 
forecast at a record level in 199091 up 2 percent from last year 
the us soybean carryover next sept 1 was projected at 265 
million bushels up 10 million from the november forecast the 
soybean inventory this sept 1 was 239 million bushels 
farm prices of soybeans were projected to average 525 to 625 
per bushel in 199091 down 10 cents on both ends of the range from 
november last season soybeans averaged 570 per bushel 
nationally at the farm 
