the plan includes a commitment to put aside oneeighth of 
canadian territory as protected space for wildlife and 
ecosystems almost double the existing 69 percent 
however that goal will require the cooperation of the 
provinces and some have already indicated they dont support it 
said lee clark parliamentary secretary to de cotret 
the green plan promises the virtual elimination of toxic 
pollution and reduction of emissions that cause groundlevel ozone 
the major ingredient in urban smog 
it sets aside 100 million for an environmental initiative in 
the arctic but offers few details on the strategy the plan also 
sets a goal of cutting canadas garbage production in half by 2000 
it promises new legislation on the safety of drinking water 
protection of wild animals and plants promotion of energy 
efficiency and dumping of waste in the oceans 
the plan promises to establish at least five new national parks 
within six years 
