<TEXT>
if anyone can get robert redford back on the 
screen its sydney pollack and the talented pair combine again 
for a drama against the backdrop of the 1958 cuban revolution 
havana 
the film marks the seventh collaboration for the unlikely pair 
the outgoing jewish hoosier and the secretive goldenhaired 
california blond 
their previous movies this property is condemned three 
days of the condor jeremiah johnson the way we were 
the electric horseman out of africa the latter winning 
pollack the 1985 academy award for director 
pollack and redford met in 1961 when both were unknown actors 
working in denis sanders antiwar film war hunt pollack had 
aimed for an acting career ever since leaving lafayette ind at 
the age of 17 and enrolling at sandford meisners neighborhood 
playhouse in new york he appeared in several broadway plays 
including stalag 17 playing the role that won william holden 
an oscar in the film version 
after two years of army service he returned to new york then 
joined john frankenheimer as dialogue coach on the film the young 
savages that led to tv directing then his first feature the 
slender thread starring sidney poitier and anne bancroft in 
1965 
his other films have included they shoot horses dont they 
absence of malice and tootsie 
pollack 56 recently talked about his relationship with redford 
and other matters in an interview with the associated press here 
are the highlights 
q its been five years since out of africa why such a gap 
between films 
a i had often threatened to set up a production company so i 
went off and did it i had always heard people say it takes so long 
to get pictures done i found out it took me three years to set up 
the company mirage we did presumed innocent major league 
the fabulous baker boys and white palace 
i didnt start looking for my own project for at least a couple 
of years then i dug up havana which i had started working on in 
1976 i didnt take the time to hunt around i just remembered 
liking it and putting it away q what was so intriguing about 
that period in havana 
a mostly it was romanticism the most sensual place in the 
world in the 50s as corrupt as any place in the world there was 
this wonderful in terms of filmmaking week of christmas 1958 
when the guns were in the hills and the gambling was at a fever 
pitch the vividness of the colors and the sensuality was like 
catnip for a filmmaker 
q did you visit havana yourself 
a many times but they the us government just wouldnt let 
me shoot there as long as youre invited and you dont spend 
money you can go there youre just not allowed to spend money 
because thats called trading with the enemy since cuba is our 
enemy they wouldnt let me spend millions of stockholders money 
down there havana was recreated in the dominican republic at an 
extra cost of 12 million to 14 million 
q how did you persuade redford to abandon his causes and skiing 
and make another movie 
a well i bought a lot of good groceries because he likes to 
eat he knows i cook pretty well and i just waved the smells and 
got him in 
no i think he welcomed the challenge of stretching a bit its 
a sleazier lowerclass character than he usually plays this guys 
a little more vulnerable hes the person who does the pursuing 
instead of the one who lays back and is the object of pursuit hes 
roughed up a little bit with a tattoo hes got some mileage on 
him now all of that certainly was good for me and i think it was 
for him too 
q what about lena olin his costar 
a lena was one of the most impressive of the newer actresses i 
had seen i needed somebody i thought could knock the pins out from 
under redford and make him drive after her through a war even 
though she was rebuffing him also she had some substance beyond 
sexuality which is not uncommon among pretty women 
q after seven pictures with redford can you work in shorthand 
a its pretty minimal whats required now sometimes i dont 
even say anything if a take of his closeup is cut and i say one 
more i dont need to say more he just knows to try something 
different 
after seven pictures and 25 years it is a shorthand that 
doesnt mean that we dont get into fights and arguments and beefs 
and i dont sometimes have to push him like hell there are always 
areas that we disagree on but hes very good about trying things 
whether he agrees or not 
