last year for the first nine months of 1990 but that the bottom 
fell out of the market in the fourth quarter which will be 
down significantly from 1989 
ad spending growth outside the united states continues to 
outpace domestic ad spending increases coen said 
he said ad spending overseas rose 126 percent to 1455 billion 
in 1990 and is expected to increase 75 percent to 1564 billion 
in 1991 
