number of dealerships owned by minority group members by 40 percent 
in three years and find ways to hang on to the 192 it already has 
the company said tuesday 
increased minority participation in our dealerships is vital 
to achieving gms prime objective of the 1990s satisfying car and 
truck owners said a statement by gm president lloyd reuss 
currently about 2 percent of gms 9600 dealers are members of 
minority groups including blacks hispanics and asians gm hopes 
to raise that number to 28 percent or 268 dealerships by 1993 
said the statement by reuss and tony march a buick dealer from 
hartford conn and chairman of the gm minority dealer advisory 
council 
about 57 percent of ford motor cos 5500 dealers are members 
of minority groups and about 25 percent of chrysler corps 5300 
dealers are from minority groups 
