phillips and drew 
theres no doubt about it the electricity shares are at the 
slightly high end of expectations wilson said but i certainly 
wouldnt say its been floated off cheaply 
the gains are not as large as they seem at first glance because 
they come on stock that is being bought with installment payments 
and because dealing costs have to be taken into account 
the shares were offered at 240 pence each or 466 payable in 
three installments the first 100 pence payment was due on 
application 
there was heightened demand for the shares however the sale of 
216 billion shares was more than 10 times oversubscribed 
prompting the government to scale back allocations to institutional 
investors 
