<TEXT>
the french national assembly adopted strict curbs 
tuesday on advertising for tobacco and alcoholic beverages over 
objections from winegrowers and sports promoters 
the assembly adopted a text worked out by a joint group of 
assembly deputies and members of the senate the approved text will 
now go to the upper chamber for consideration 
the law forbids all forms of direct or indirect tobacco 
advertising beginning jan 1 1993 and orders steep hikes in the 
price of cigarettes 
it is less severe on alcohol taking into account the concerns 
of senators from winegrowing regions who caused stiffer measures to 
be rejected in an earlier bill in october 
the revised version permits advertising in wineproducing 
regions in the written press aimed at adults and in certain radio 
broadcasts 
senators on the joint committee expressed confidence the 
proposal will pass their chamber later this month 
sponsorship by alcoholic beverage or tobacco companies in sports 
and other events will be strictly forbidden 
health minister claude evin who has pushed the advertising 
restrictions for a year calls such tobacco or alcohol sponsorship 
advertising in disguise 
the measures irritated jeanmarie balestre president of the 
international federation of auto sports the motor racing industry 
is heavily dependent on tobacco sponsorship 
there is too much hypocrisy in these measures he declared 
monday during an awards ceremony there are other much more 
dangerous scourges like drugs 
some deputies who voted against the bill tuesday remarked that 
the way to cure alcohol or tobacco abuse lay in better education 
others said it would cause unemployment in wineproducing areas 
evin says the law is necessary to bring down consumption of 
tobacco and alcohol by young french people and has praised the 
success of antitobacco campaigns in the united states 
