23 berger said of that total 14 were americans and nine were 
japanese he said 
the evidence showed that quasar had full knowledge of the laws 
which prohibit discrimination and yet it tried to circumvent these 
laws berger said the court found that quasar would not have 
fired any of our clients but for their national origin 
in a 1988 ruling a jury awarded 19 million to the plaintiffs 
in settlement of the age discrimination lawsuit all three were 
over 50 at the time of their dismissal the three were told that 
their jobs were being eliminated but their functions were 
reassigned to younger people berger said 
us district judge james alesia upheld the jurys 1988 decision 
in posttrial motions and assessed additional fines in the 
nationality discrimination case friday 
quasar based in suburban elk grove village handles sales and 
distribution of consumer electronics and employees about 50 people 
the company is a division of the japaneseowned matsushita electric 
corp of america 
